More than 150, 000 sheep and goats have been vaccinated against waterborne diseases as rains pound Samburu county. The sheep and goat pox vaccination targets more than 300, 000 sheep and goat in Samburu Central and East. The project is being led by Caritas Maralal, an NGO funded by the Catholic Church. Livestock owners said the vaccination will prevent animal deaths, especially when drought strikes. Rahab Lebeiya of Lkuroto village in Samburu Central said they have been losing their goats and sheep to diseases in the past.